In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @Sriracha{1%tsp} to taste.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and a big pinch of @salt{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @shredded carrots{4%oz}, @sesame dressing{1.5%oz}, @sweet soy glaze{2 1/2%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Cook until carrots are softened, pork is cooked through, and sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork if preferred.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between bowls; top with pork mixture and any remaining sauce from pan. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Sprinkle with @wonton strips{1%oz} and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Ground turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.